It helps to make a code in easy way or with help of ternary operator we can wrtie a 4 code line in one line or rather use of if-else we can use ternary operator.
it is only for simple conditions .
we cant not execute many conditions.
command is :- Condition ? do something if true : do something if false;

for example : write a code if marks >30 pass and fail if marks <=30
#include<stdio.h>
int main()
{
    int marks;
    printf("enter marks (0-100)");
    scanf("%d",&marks);

    /*if (marks>30 && marks<=100){
        printf("pass");
    }
    else if (marks<=30){
        printf("fail");
    }
    else{
        printf("back");
    }*/

    marks >=30  ? printf("pass"):printf("fail");
    
}
